Lemma: Probability bound from uniform continuity on a set.
If `f` maps `δ`-close points to `ε`-close points when the second point is in `K`,
then `P(dist (f X) (f Y) > ε) ≤ P(dist X Y ≥ δ) + P(Y ∉ K)`.
